AbatabDataRoot

The root directory where non-web service data code is located.

Declaration
public string AbatabDataRoot { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.String

Default value is C:\AbatabData
Remarks
  • At runtime the AvatarEnvironment value is created as a sub-directory of the AbatabDataRoot.
  • This is the directory where exported data/logs should be stored.
Examples

If AbatabDataRoot=C:\AbatabData, and AvatarEnvironment=LIVE, then AbatabDataRoot would be set to C:\AbatabData\LIVE at runtime.

AbatabMode

The mode that Abatab will use when executed.

Declaration
public string AbatabMode { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.String

Default value is enabled
Remarks

SettingDescription
enabledAll Abatab functionality is (potentially) available.
disabledAbatab functionality is not available.
passthroughAll functionality is available, but no changes are made to Avatar.
  • If this is set to AbatabMode=enabled, you are still able to disable specific modules via their corresponding mode setting.
  • The AbatabMode=passthrough mode is intended for development, not production.

AbatabServiceRoot

The root directory where the Abatab web service has been deployed.

Declaration
public string AbatabServiceRoot { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.String

Default value is C:\Abatab_
Remarks
  • At runtime the AvatarEnvironment value is added to the end of AbatabRoot to form the complete path.
Examples

If AbatabRoot=C:\Abatab_, and AvatarEnvironment=LIVE, then AbatabRoot would be set to C:\Abatab_LIVE at runtime.

Declaration
public string AbatabUserName { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.String

Set at runtime.
Remarks
  • This should be set to the value in sentOptObj.OptionUserId.
  • If the value in sentOptObj.OptionUserId is not valid, this will be set to AbatabFallbackUserName.
